# QuantForg Trading OS — baseline discipline

P0 is the baseline. `tsc --noEmit` must stay clean.

## Priority order (never invert)

1. Preserve production functionality
2. Preserve MT5 execution
3. Preserve backend contracts
4. Preserve authentication
5. Remove mock/demo UI (real data or empty states)
6. Collapse duplicate workflows
7. Eight primary surfaces only (Terminal, Book, Research, Counsel, Journal, Broker, Inbox, Settings)
8. Institutional design system (IBM Plex Sans/Mono, steel tokens; no neon/atmosphere gradients)
9. Terminal is flagship
10. Continuously releasable repository

## Do not touch unless explicitly asked

Backend, APIs, database, auth, MT5 gateway, Cloudflare, Railway, order execution, websockets, TradingView integration, Supabase protocol.

## Quality gate (before every commit)

Run and fix until green:

- TypeScript (`tsc --noEmit`) — zero errors; never weaken types
- ESLint
- Production build
- Unit tests
- GitHub Actions must be expected green

Never introduce new TypeScript errors. Never reduce type safety.
Every redesign phase must finish production-ready before the next begins.

P1–P4 flagship desks: Terminal, Book, Research, Counsel.
P4.5 Design Bible is binding (`docs/design/`, ADR-0022).
Do not modify `components/terminal/`, `book/`, `research/`, or `counsel/` unless explicitly asked.
Future features must pass Design Bible + acceptance checklists.

See `docs/adr/0016`–`0022` and `docs/design/README.md`.
